# Overview

This is my first attempt to create the course website.

# Getting Started

## Install and launching R packages

The code chunk below uses p_load() of pacman package to check if tidyverse packages are installed in the computer. If they are, then they will be launched into R.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse) 
```
:::


## The Data

Importing the data


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exam_data <- read_csv("data/Exam_data.csv")
```
:::


# Data Visualization

Plotting a simple bar chart


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HE01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data = exam_data,
       aes(x = RACE)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = "steelblue4", color = "grey40") +
  labs(
    x = "Race",
    y = "Number of Students"
  ) +
  theme(
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white")
  ) +
  coord_flip()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HE01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, 
       aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_dotplot(binwidth=2.5,         
               dotsize = 0.5) +      
  scale_y_continuous(NULL,           
                     breaks = NULL)  
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HE01_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672}
